	(text "SPI COMMUNICATION\nPROTOCOL\n\nSCLK => SCLK\nDIN => TO MOSI\nDOUT =>TO MISO\nCS => CS"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 250.952 55.626 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(thickness 0.254)
				(bold yes)
			)
		)
		(uuid "1103617a-2df7-45d8-a186-c63028d4d75e")
	)
	(text "This ADC configuration is meant to be use in Single-Side mode,\nin order to measure current with AIN0-AINCOM and potential in\nthe cell with AIN1-AINCOM when doing a voltamperommetric\nexperiment. For another type of experiment, it may use a \ndifferent approach."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 70.104 143.002 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(face "KiCad Font")
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(thickness 0.254)
				(bold yes)
			)
		)
		(uuid "52e73f5b-796a-44de-ba21-667ee7802df5")
	)
	(text "XTAL1/CLKIN PIN CAN BE USED AS A CLK INPUT FOR ADS1255\nTHIS WAS ALREADY TESTED WITH AN ESP32 GENERATING A \n7.8MHZ CLOCK AND ADS1255 WORKS GOOD. TAKE INTO ACCOUNT\nTHIS OPTION IF YOU WISH TO AVOID THE XTAL OPTION\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 227.584 142.24 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(thickness 0.254)
				(bold yes)
				(color 255 0 11 1)
			)
		)
		(uuid "56d06b41-10f1-4ae1-bca3-86528970d3b8")
	)
	(text "I PERSONALLY RECOMMEND TO FOLLOW ADS1255 DATASHEET'S \nRECOMMENDATION FOR CRYSTALS. AS I HAVE EXPERIENCED TROUBLE\nTRYING TO GET A GENERIC 8 MHZ CRYSTAL TO WORKS.\nPCB LAYOUT DOENS'T SEEMS PROBLEMATIC TO MY UNDERSTANDING.\nYOU CAN ALSO CHECK THE APPLICATION REPORT SBAA104 FROM\nTEXAS INSTRUMENTS CALLED \n\"Using Ceramic Resonators with the ADS1255/6\""
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 228.854 155.448 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(thickness 0.254)
				(bold yes)
			)
		)
		(uuid "98ecf756-22c1-446a-a47b-204e30c76490")
	)
